OL,3,CThe Herring Girls who helped the North
OL,4,CShields Fish Quay boom
OL,6,F"You wouldn't think it, but they
OL,7,Fseemed to be a very joyful bunch. They
OL,8,Fwould come down and be singing, they'd
OL,9,Fbe carrying on, but they weren't to be
OL,10,Fcrossed. That's what I tried to get
OL,11,Facross."
OL,13,FThe women were known for their sharp
OL,14,Fknives, and their sharp tongues, and
OL,15,Fproved that the world of fishing was
OL,16,Fnot only for men.
OL,18,FHistorian Rory Page told ITV Tyne Tees
OL,19,Fthe job was not for the faint-hearted.
